Fields.Name: ATOMIC
Fields.Documentation: Set this bit to start an automatic atomic calibration of the IPO. The calibration runs for FCR_AUTOCAL2.donecnt milliseconds. This bit is automatically cleared by hardware when the calibration is complete.

Fields.Name: TRIM
Fields.Description: HIRC96M Trim Value Determinged by Auto Calibration
Fields.Documentation: HIRC96M Trim Value Determinged by Auto Calibration.

Fields.Name: INITIAL
Fields.Description: IPO Trim Automatic Calibration Initial Trim
Fields.Documentation: This field contains the initial trim setting for the IPO. Set this field to the desired initial trim value to use for an IPO automatic calibration operation. The closer this field is to the target trim value required, the faster the automatic trim operation completes.

Fields.Name: RUNTIME
Fields.Description: IPO Trim Automatic Calibration Run Time
Fields.Documentation: Set this field to the desired number of milliseconds for the atomic calibration runtime for the IPO.

Fields.Name: DIV
Fields.Description: IPO Trim Automatic Calibration Divide Factor
Fields.Documentation: The target frequency of the calibration is determined by dividing the IPO frequency by 32,768 before comparing it with the ERTCO frequency. For example, to achieve a target IPO frequency of 100MHz, load this field with 0xBEB (3,051).

Fields.Name: WR
Fields.Documentation: This bit is automatically cleared after the operation.

Fields.Name: ME
Fields.Documentation: This bit is automatically cleared after the operation.

Fields.Name: PGE
Fields.Documentation: This bit is automatically cleared after the operation.

Fields.Name: ERASE_CODE
Fields.Documentation: The ERASE_CODE must be set up property before erase operation can be initiated. These bits are automatically cleared after the operation is complete.

Enum.Name: ERASEALL
Enum.Documentation: The debug port must be enabled.

Fields.Name: PEND
Fields.Documentation: When Flash operation is in progress (busy), Flash reads and writes will fail. When PEND is set, write to all Flash registers, with exception of the Flash interrupt register, are ignored.

Fields.Name: UNLOCK
Fields.Documentation: The correct unlock code must be written to these four bits before any Flash write or erase operation is allowed.

Fields.Name: DONE
Fields.Documentation: This bit is set to 1 upon Flash write or erase completion.

Fields.Name: AF
Fields.Documentation: This bit is set when an attempt is made to write the flash while the flash is busy or the flash is locked. This bit can only be set to 1 by hardware.

Fields.Name: SYSCLK_DIV
Fields.Documentation: This 3 bit field sets the system operating frequency by controlling the prescaler that divides the output of the PLL0.

Fields.Name: SYSCLK_SEL
Fields.Documentation: This 3 bit field selects the source for the system clock.

Fields.Name: SYSCLK_RDY
Fields.Documentation: This read only bit reflects whether the currently selected system clock source is running.

Enum.Documentation: Switchover to the New Clock Source (as Selected by CLKSEL) Has Not Yet Occurred.

Enum.Documentation: System Clock Running from CLKSEL Clock Source.

Fields.Name: IBRO_VS
Fields.Description: 7.3725 MHz High Frequency Internal Reference Clock Voltage Select
Fields.Documentation: This register bit is used to select the power supply to the IBRO.

Fields.Name: INRO_RDY
Fields.Description: 8 KHz Low Frequency Reference Clock Ready
Fields.Documentation: 8 KHz Low Frequency Reference Clock Ready.

Fields.Name: EXTCLK_RDY
Fields.Documentation: Clock is ready when AF2 is enabled for GPIO0_28.

Fields.Name: AON_CLKDIV
Fields.Documentation: These bits define the AON domain clock divider.

Fields.Name: MODE
Fields.Documentation: This two bit field selects the current operating mode for the device. Note that code execution only occurs during ACTIVE mode.

Fields.Name: GPIO_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables all GPIO pins as potential wakeup sources. Any GPIO configured for wakeup is capable of causing an exit from IDLE or STANDBY modes when this bit is set.

Fields.Name: RTC_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables RTC alarm as wakeup source. If enabled, the desired RTC alarm must be configured via the RTC control registers.

Fields.Name: LPTMR0_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables TIMER4 as wakeup source.

Fields.Name: LPTMR1_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables TIMER5 as wakeup source.

Fields.Name: LPUART0_WE
Fields.Documentation: This bit enables LPUART3 as wakeup source.

Fields.Name: ERFO_PD
Fields.Documentation: This bit selects 32MHz Crystal power state in DEEPSLEEP mode.

Fields.Name: IPO_PD
Fields.Documentation: This bit selects IPO clock power state in DEEPSLEEP mode.

Fields.Name: IBRO_PD
Fields.Documentation: This bit selects 7.3725 MHz clock power state in DEEPSLEEP mode.

Fields.Name: ERFO_BP
Fields.Documentation: This bit is set to 0 on a POR is not affected by other forms of reset. Set this field to 1 to use a square wave input as the clock source for the ERFO driving the HFXIN pin.
